  "50007": {
    "categorized": true,
    "category": 1,
    "cc": null,
    "date": "Tue, 29 Apr 2014 20:05:58 -0400",
    "from": "Nick Shelly <nshelly@stanford.edu>",
    "id": 50007,
    "message": "Hi Luke,\r\n\r\nI hope everything is going well for you!  I was hoping to catch up with you and see if you knew what you were doing yet after graduation?  I remember you\u2019ve done a number of successful web-based projects but also have a strong systems background, so we thought you would be a good fit for our company.\r\n\r\nI just took a leave of absence to join a networking startup out of Nick McKeown\u2019s group (his most recent company Nicira was acquired last year by VMware for $1.5B+).  Nick, Mendel Rosenblum and Diane Greene of VMware are early angel investors.  We are only 2 employees plus the co-founders, 4 Stanford PhDs with experience at Google and other leading networking companies.  We\u2019re hoping to launch the full product as soon as possible and have large customers ready to pay (it\u2019s basically a $200B industry).  It\u2019s early enough where there is still a opportunity to shape the company, and tackle some really hard algorithms while using the latest web tech (we\u2019re using Java, Python and JavaScript right now).  We\u2019re planning to close Series A with some of the top VCs by the end of the year, so there is still a significant amount of equity and leadership opportunities available.\r\n\r\nI\u2019m sure you have quite a few options, including starting your own, but if you\u2019re interested in learning more, I can put you in touch with the team.  I\u2019m out of town until a week from Monday, but either way, it would be great to catch up.\r\n\r\nTake care,\r\nNick\r\n\r\n\r\n",
    "predicted": true,
    "read": false,
    "subject": "Startup opportunity",
    "to": "lukeknepper@gmail.com"
  },
