    "id": 50121,
    "message": "<div dir=\"ltr\"><div><div>Friends --<br><br></div>Steve Long had a massive heart attack last week in Taiwan; he has thankfully passed the critical stage but needs prayers to stabilize and for complete healing.\u00a0 Vicky went to Taiwan on the day he had surgery and only found out when she disembarked.\u00a0 She is now doing all the meetings but her foot is swollen so please pray for her as well.<br>\r\n<br></div>Here are some specifics from Vicky; if you want more details on Steve let me know:<br><br>It was recommended that I attend our meetings and give the speeches and \r\nmessages because, I cannot see him. \u00a0He gets too emotional when he sees \r\nvisitors and it disrupts his peaceful time of resting and healing. \u00a0So \r\nwe have staff who are keeping close watch while he sleeps. I am doing \r\nthe meetings - a full schedule.<br><br>Please pray with us for Steve&#39;s complete healing asap. <br><br>Please pray for me to have the ability to do all the meetings and have a very inspiring message from God for everyone.<br>\r\n<br>Peter\r\n and John are doing very well at Becky&#39;s home. \u00a0I am able to skype and \r\ntalk with them. Please pray for them to be at peace and be able to focus\r\n on getting their end of year school testing done well.<br><br>Thank you again for your prayer support. It is greatly appreciated.<br><br>God\r\n is good all the time. He has a purpose and plan for everything. There \r\nis a time and a season for all things. We pray that you are in a good \r\nseason with God Your loving heavenly Father.<br><br>Blessings<br>Vicky<br clear=\"all\"><div><div><div><br>-- <br>Stephanie Kirtland<br>650-561-3536\r\n</div></div></div></div>\r\n",
    "predicted": true,
    "read": false,
    "subject": "Prayers for Steve Long",
