  "50404": {
    "categorized": true,
    "category": 2,
    "cc": null,
    "date": "Mon, 19 May 2014 05:26:22 -0600",
    "from": "James F Walker <James.F.Walker@Colorado.EDU>",
    "id": 50404,
    "message": "Dear Enid,\r\nWe're in.\r\n-Bubba\r\n\r\nPS: Bethany, cannot wait to meet you!\r\n\r\nPPS: You're rocking your life right now, Enid! Careful not to blow a gasket. ;-)\r\n\r\n\r\n________________________________________\r\nFrom: Luke Knepper [lukeknepper@gmail.com]\r\nSent: Saturday, May 17, 2014 12:48 PM\r\nTo: Bethany\r\nSubject: Dates & Updates, Luke & Bethany\r\n\r\nHi extended family, near and far!\r\n\r\nI hope & pray that you're doing well -- I'm just past mid-terms and in the final few weeks of my undergrad career, crazy times.\r\n\r\nBethany and I want to let you know about a few dates and updates in our future...\r\n\r\nGraduation! I'm graduating on June 15th and you are all invited. I've put more info at the end of the email...\r\n\r\nWedding! Our wedding is on August 10th in Dallas, TX, and you're all invited! You should have received a Save the Date in the mail and will get an invitation soon. We will also have a California reception in Marin on September 20th.\r\n\r\nSan Francisco! This week I accepted a full-time software development position at BrightRoll<http://brightroll.com> in San Francisco! God provided us with an amazing opportunity. We're really excited to move up to the city and are hoping to live in the Mission District for the next two years. We think it will give Bethany tons of opportunities in the art world and give us a chance to minister to the \"least churched city in the country.\"\r\n\r\nBusiness School! I have been offered deferred admission to Stanford Graduate School of Business! The plan is for me to start in the fall of 2016 (so we will move back to the Stanford area then) and graduate with my MBA in 2018. This is a while down the road, but we're super excited and thankful.\r\n\r\nThat's it for now... much love, and looking forward to seeing you this summer.\r\n\r\nLuke & Bethany\r\n\r\n\"In his heart a man plans his course, but the LORD determines his steps.\" Proverbs 16:9\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\nGraduation Info\r\nBill and Melinda Gates are speaking at Commencement, 9:30am to 11:30am in the football stadium. Commencement info available online<https://commencement.stanford.edu/>.\r\n\r\nMy Computer Science ceremony (where I get my degree) is at 12:15pm (until perhaps 1:30pm) in Frost Amphitheater, lunch and drinks are provided. More info online<http://www-cs.stanford.edu/commencement>.\r\n\r\nNo tickets are needed, but let me know if you're planning to come!\r\n\r\nAfterwards, the plan is to go up to Grammee's in Marin and have a late lunch of Chinese food. There may also be parties or events the night before...more plans coming.\r\n",
    "predicted": true,
    "read": false,
    "subject": "RE: Dates & Updates, Luke & Bethany",
    "to": "Luke Knepper <lukeknepper@gmail.com>, Bethany <bethanyjoyeden@gmail.com>"
  },
